<subSubSection id="51C1CE923890305AA8CF39E2EE6BCD12" pageNumber="263" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1E85A470EE0AE365089658869AF0042F" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="74C8D8321A381EB207203A115800FCD0" italics="true" pageNumber="263">Note:</emphasis>
Tryon (in 
<emphasis id="F1C07018101A1B6DBFD9A6CD6B7FFBBB" italics="true" pageNumber="263">Contr. Gray Herb.</emphasis>
194: 152. 1964) treated 1252.10 (LINN) as the type but Proctor (in Howard, 
<emphasis id="2E10116EDF43928186059FF5BD71F18E" italics="true" pageNumber="263">Fl. Lesser Antilles</emphasis>
2: 185. 1977) argued that both it and the cited Plukenet plate conflicted with 
<normalizedToken id="047D51C3E4CF4229736A7E3C5DAF8A54" originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
diagnosis and so designated a 
<typeStatus id="F20B0CA35AF27AEA64958F45EA4A842E">neotype</typeStatus>
from Herb. Sloane (1: 127, BM-SL). The material in LINN is apparently identifiable as 
<taxonomicName id="88191FCF680516C89AE358A487EC0910" authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Adiantum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulverulentum">
<emphasis id="8D09B5763205CFA6B72623F2B8EE20E5" italics="true" pageNumber="263">A. pulverulentum</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, while the Plukenet plate is said to depict 
<taxonomicName id="F6DCE69E70D626DCE59505C2FBAC3485" authority="Jenman" authorityName="Jenman" authorityYear="1886" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Pteridaceae" genus="Adiantum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Polypodiales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kendalii">
<emphasis id="E4288D0CDB658E76E45A18ABBD74A5A5" italics="true" pageNumber="263">A. kendalii</emphasis>
Jenman
</taxonomicName>
(Proctor, 
<emphasis id="925AFA9FA6AEFD1FAF4EF232CC8E18B0" italics="true" pageNumber="263">Ferns Jamaica:</emphasis>
241. 1985). However, despite its apparently unfortunate identity, the Plukenet element forms part of the protologue and therefore cannot be deemed to conflict with it. It is original material for the name, and so 
<normalizedToken id="D68BD27AD81815502378946D6E7183F7" originalValue="Proctor’s">Proctor's</normalizedToken>
designation of a 
<typeStatus id="3B7F5AA6BB333D017B346ECDC65F7225">neotype</typeStatus>
is contrary to Art. 7.11. The name may be a candidate for conservation with a conserved type.
</paragraph>
